    Scope and Contents
TELEPHONE PROJECT 
Fitzgerald, employee of Illinois Bell Telephone Company, discusses his experiences working for Illinois Bell. He recalls a fire at the company offices in 1927, effects of the Depression and WWII, customer billing procedures, changes in technology, and a 1947 strike. Also mentions Springfield transportation developments. 1 tape, 70 mins, 23 pp
Interview by Thomas Easley, 1973 
